Detailed Description

Process Logs Iterates through each log entry and processes entry/exit pairs to calculate time elapsed, total calls, and iterations while resolving the name of each function for the final printout.

Note:

  • "Calls" are defined as instrumented function calls that are made by a given function
  • "Cycles" are the total number of processor ticks elapsed by the function
  • "Iterations" are the number of references, or times the single function is called
